<p>First i read the image using </p>  <p><code>img&lt;-readPNG(imageLocation)</code></p>  <p>imageLocation is the path of the image location with path.expand()</p>  <pre><code>imageLocation = path.expand("~/R/funwithR/data/mero_photoforanalysis.png") </code></pre>  <p>Converting to grayscale is done by</p>  <pre><code>img &lt;- 0.2126 * img[, , 1] + 0.7152 * img[, , 2] + 0.0722 * img[, , 3] </code></pre>  <p>finally error is given by</p>  <pre><code>face_emotion(img) </code></pre>  <p>The error is </p>  <pre><code>Error in function (type, msg, asError = TRUE)  : couldn't connect to host </code></pre>